05/08/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Macedonia and Albania will soon start negotiations on opening two new border crossings between the two countries, the Albanian Daily News reported Wednesday (4 August). 
The agreement on principle was reached during a meeting Tuesday between Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami and his Macedonian counterpart, Ilinka Mitreva. 
The two ministers also vowed to boost bilateral co-operation in order to accelerate progress in EU and NATO integration efforts. 
(Albanian Daily News - 05/08/04)
